                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15512775" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2016 09:41:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What is the MongoDB version you are using?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15512884" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2016 10:24:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are most likely running MongoDB with authentication enabled and the user connecting to MongoDB does not have the &apos;clusterAdmin&apos; role assigned.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15513173" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2016 12:34:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;MongoDocumentStore now falls back to the &lt;tt&gt;buildInfo&lt;/tt&gt; command to get the version if &lt;tt&gt;serverStatus&lt;/tt&gt; does not return it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixed in trunk: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1761930&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1761930&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Giovanni, thanks for reporting this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15513207" author="landolina.giovanni" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2016 12:47:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I thought I wrote that.. MongoDB 3.2.9, driver 3.2.2/3.3.0.&lt;br/&gt;
I tried and play with the clusterMonitor role yesterday, with no luck.&lt;br/&gt;
I just tried with clusterAdmin&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;db.createUser({user: &apos;$MONGODB_USER&apos;, pwd: &apos;$MONGODB_PASS&apos;, roles:[&lt;/p&gt;
{role:&apos;clusterAdmin&apos;,db:&apos;admin&apos;}
&lt;p&gt;, &lt;/p&gt;
{role:&apos;clusterMonitor&apos;,db:&apos;admin&apos;}
&lt;p&gt;, &lt;/p&gt;
{role:&apos;root&apos;,db:&apos;admin&apos;}
&lt;p&gt;]&lt;br/&gt;
});&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but again, no success.&lt;br/&gt;
Is the mongodb configuration detailed somewhere in the docs? I &apos;ve not been able to find it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15513221" author="landolina.giovanni" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2016 12:51:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the fix, Marcel!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15513250" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2016 13:04:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See for example this &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/20879277/how-to-get-number-of-connections-to-mongodb-when-auth-true&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;post on stackoverflow&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15544784" author="edivad" created="Tue, 4 Oct 2016 08:48:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for 1.5.11&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
